Global Radioligand Therapy Market Insights
Radioligand Therapy Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 15.0% from 2024 to 2030.

Radioligand Therapy Market Overview
The global radioligand therapy market size was valued at USD 4.3 billion in 2024 and is expected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 18.5% from 2024 to 2030. This growth is primarily driven by the rising incidence of cancer, advancements in radiopharmaceuticals, and increasing adoption of personalized therapies. The market is characterized by innovations in targeting specific cancer cells with minimal damage to surrounding tissues, leading to more effective and safer treatment options. Additionally, the increasing prevalence of diseases such as prostate cancer and neuroendocrine tumors has fueled the demand for radioligand therapy, offering a promising solution in oncology treatment.

